author: Salman Khan
title: Late Geelong President Frank Costa's Family Pledges $10 Million to Boost Club's Future
text:
The family of the late Geelong Football Club president Frank Costa has made an unprecedented $10 million pledge to the club, marking a significant contribution to its future and honoring Costa's lasting legacy. This generous donation, confirmed by Costa's widow Shirley at a recent club function, is set to propel the development of a new indoor training facility, a testament to Costa's lifelong devotion to the Cats and the broader Geelong community.
Monumental Legacy and Transformation
Frank Costaâ€™s tenure as president beginning in 1999 was a turning point for the Geelong Football Club. At a time when the club faced financial difficulties and on-field struggles, Costa, alongside CEO Brian Cook, spearheaded a dramatic turnaround. Their leadership not only rescued the club from financial despair but also laid the foundations for a golden era, culminating in premiership victories in 2007 and 2009, and once again in 2011. Costa's vision and dedication transformed the club into one of the AFL's most formidable forces, breaking a premiership drought that had lingered since 1963 and reinvigorating the spirit of the Geelong community.
Tributes and Honors
Frank Costaâ€™s impact extended beyond the football field. His passing in May 2021, after a prolonged illness, was met with an outpouring of tributes from across Victoria and the football community. Recognized for his contributions to both the club and the town of Geelong, Costa was honored with a state memorial service held at Kardinia Park, attended by thousands. In 2023, the city further commemorated his legacy by unveiling a statue in the city center, capturing Costa in his early days as a local paper boy. This gesture symbolized Costa's humble beginnings and his profound influence on the Geelong community.
A Bright Future Ahead
With the announcement of the Costa family's $10 million donation, the Geelong Football Club embarks on a new chapter, one that promises to build on Frank Costaâ€™s remarkable legacy. The planned indoor training facility is just one aspect of the clubâ€™s future development plans, aimed at enhancing the teamâ€™s training capabilities and securing its competitive edge. As the Cats prepare to unveil their new Selwood Stand at GMHBA stadium in the opening round against St Kilda, increasing the venue's capacity to over 40,000, the spirit of Frank Costaâ€™s dedication and passion for the club lives on, driving Geelong towards a future filled with promise and success.

author: Sumit Rajan
title: Angel Reese Could Get Too Good to Be in Chicago Sky Soon - NewsBreak
text: On Tuesday evening in Minnesota, Angel Reese made WNBA history once again by achieving her 10th consecutive double-double, finishing the game with 11 points, 11 rebounds, and 3 assists in a lopsided 98-61 defeat against the Lynx. This achievement makes her the only player in WNBA history to have multiple streaks of 10 or more consecutive double-doubles. Reeseâ€™s performance stood out amidst the struggles of the 7-16 Chicago Sky , who have had a tough time winning this season. Her exceptional rebounding skills have been a consistent aspect of her game, and while some critics refer to her as a â€œme-boundingâ€ stat-padder, her results speak volumes. Reese is currently leading the league in rebounds and has shattered several rookie records in 2024, including the most double-doubles by a rookie (26) and the most total rebounds in a single season (446). Additionally, she now holds the record for the most consecutive double-doubles in a season with 15, achieved earlier this year. Although Tuesday nightâ€™s performance did not alter the outcome for the Sky, it served as another indication that Reese is rapidly establishing her legacy while under significant scrutiny. Even in the loss, Reese distinguished herself through her hustle and determination, albeit with some areas for improvement. She committed nine turnovers against the Lynx, which continues to be a challenge for her this season, as she currently leads the league in turnovers. However, according to Collier, this is all part of the development process. The post Angel Reese Could Get Too Good to Be in Chicago Sky Soon appeared first on BlackSportsOnline .
